e real names in examples\n- Added export function to plan (dm/group, peer/date structure)\n\n## 9:04 PM\n- Allan: Should separate DM and group\n- Updated export structure: `dm/{peer}/` and `group/{name}/`\n\n## 9:09 PM\n- Discussed folder structure: `year/month/date` vs `year-month/date`\n- Decided: Keep `year-month/date` (current structure)\n\n## 9:13 PM\n- Listed all LCM changes:\n  1. New `contacts` table\n  2. Add `peer_id`, `chat_type` to `conversations`\n  3. Peer extraction logic\n  4. Export function (dm/group, peer/date)\n  5. Enhanced search with peer filtering\n- Ready to implement\n\n## 9:13 PM (Heartbeat)\n- LCM enhancement plan finalized with Allan\n- Ready to fork LCM and implement changes\n\n## 9:24 PM\n- Allan: CLI should have export MD option\n- Added CLI export command to plan:\n  - `lcm export --output ./exports`\n  - `lcm export --peer alice`\n  - `lcm export --chat-type dm`\n  - `lcm export --from --to` date range\n\n## 9:28 PM (Heartbeat)\n- LCM enhancement plan complete\n- Added CLI export command\n- Ready to implement\n\n## 9:36 PM\n- Allan: One ID can have multiple channels (feishu, telegram, tui)\n- Updated contacts table: PRIMARY KEY (peer_id, channel)\n- Allan: Export should show channel, time, name\n- Format: `[channel] time name: message`\n\n## 9:41 PM\n- Finalized export format: `[Feishu] 14:30 Alice: Hello`\n- Simple, compact, readable\n- Ready to implement\n\n## 9:43 PM (Heartbeat)\n- LCM enhancement design complete\n- Schema: contacts (peer_id, peer_name, channel) with composite PK\n- Export format: `[channel] time name: message`\n- Ready to fork and implement\n\n## 9:46 PM\n- Allan: Can peer_id be duplicate?\n- Explained: Composite PK (peer_id, channel) allows same person on multiple channels\n\n## 9:50 PM\n- Allan: Does composite PK work? What is contacts.channels for?\n- Clarified: SQLite supports composite PK\n- Simplified design: channel belongs in `conversations`, not `contacts`\n- Revised schema:\n  - `contacts`: peer_id (PK